cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with deep convolutional semantic segmentation (DCSS) learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a joint cooperative end-to-end learning method that simultaneously learns segmentation and classification, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML) and specifically, deep learning (DL). Hence, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces an improved inception-based architecture with partial attention gating (PAG), which involves attention mechanisms and gating functions, both of which are popular in natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, cs.NE and cs.CL are also possible sub-categories.
